org.biojava.nbio.structure.contact

Class GroupContactSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.biojava.nbio.structure.contact.GroupContactSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<GroupContact>

    public class GroupContactSet
extends Object
implements Serializable, Iterable<GroupContact>
    A set of residue-residue contacts. Relies on residue indices (based on SEQRES and starting with 1) to store the pairs and thus to match contacts.
    Author:
    duarte_j
    See Also:
    ResidueIdentifier, Serialized Form

      Constructors

      GroupContactSet() 
      GroupContactSet(AtomContactSet atomContacts)
      Constructs a GroupContactSet by collapsing the given AtomContactSet into residue-residue (group-group) contacts.

      Tell whether the given group pair is a contact in this GroupContactSet, the comparison is done by matching residue numbers and chain identifiers

      Tell whether the given pair is a contact in this GroupContactSet, in a chain-identifier independent way: contacts happening between different copies of the same Compound(Entity) will be considered equal as long as they have the same residue numbers.
